            %li
              %h3 Eligibility
              %p The Great Race (the Contest) is open to legal residents of the fifty (50) United States and the District of Columbia who are at least eighteen (18) years old at the time of entry. Volunteers & Contractors of FoodCircles LLC and other companies associated with the promotion of the Contest, and their respective parents, subsidiaries, affiliates and advertising and promotion agencies as well as the immediate family (spouse, parents, siblings, and children) and household members of each such person are not eligible. The Contest is subject to federal, state, and local laws and regulations.
            %li
              %h3 Sponsor
              %p The Sweepstakes is sponsored by FoodCircles LLC, located at 38 Fulton W, Grand Rapids, Michigan 49503.
            %li
              %h3 Agreement to Official Rules
              %p Participation in the Sweepstakes constitutes entrants full and unconditional agreement to and acceptance of these Official Rules and the decisions of the Sponsor, which are final and binding. Winning a prize is contingent upon being compliant with these Official Rules and fulfilling all other requirements set forth herein.
            %li
              %h3 Contest Period
              %p The Contest begins on May 22, 2012 at 12:00pm EST and ends on June 05, 2012 at 12:00pm EST (the Contest Period). Entries that are submitted before or after the Contest Period will be disqualified. Submissions will be accepted for the duration of the Contest using the web application at http://foodcircles.net, http://m.foodcircles.net, or the downloadable applications on Android and iOS.
            %li
              %h3 How to Enter
              %p The method of entry will be available by visiting our website (http://foodcircles.net) or downloading our mobile apps.  Entrant should pick an available restaurant, perk, and charity as the app dictates, create an account, and download a voucher for their outing.  With a group of up to 6 people total, redeem the voucher before the specified expiry time by purchasing a regular meal for each person, and receiving a complimentary side item (the restaurant will donate the cost to provide 1 meal for a person in need through your selected charity).  Limit one (1) entry per person, per email address, and per household for the duration of the Sweepstakes Period, regardless of method of entry. Entries received from any person, e-mail address, or household in excess of the stated limitation will be void. All entries become the property of Sponsor and will not be acknowledged or returned.
            %li
              %h3 How to Redeem
              %p
                Keep all receipts/proofs of purchase! You will not be eligible to receive a reimbursement check without it!  The number of compensated meals available is equal to the number of FoodCircles Restaurant partners.  One (1) compensated meal is available per restaurant.  To receive a reimbursement check, entrant must be the first to dine at the restaurant using a valid voucher from FoodCircles after the start of The Great Race, and before the end of The Great Race.  Before June 05, 2012, entrant must submit a photo, or scanned copy, of the receipt onto either a personal Facebook.com page or a personal Twitter.com page.  The entrant must "tag" and/or "mention" FoodCircles in the posting of the image.  A successful "tag" on Facebook will require the account to have "Liked" the FoodCircles Facebook page.  FoodCircles LLC reserves the right to demand further proof, resubmission, or original copy in order to verify accuracy of the receipt.  If verified to be accurate AND if the first receipt "posted" on
                Facebook or Twitter from a previously unclaimed FoodCircles restaurant, FoodCircles LLC will contact, via electronic media, the entrant requesting the entrant's mailing address.  A list of claimed and unclaimed FoodCircles Restaurants will be made available on the FoodCircles website.  FoodCircles LLC will write & dispatch one (1) reimbursement check for the amount listed on the receipt, or the listed limit on our website, whichever is lower.  FoodCircles LLC is not responsible for an inaccuracy in the given address, failed delivery/receipt, lost mail, etc. If the potential winner cannot be contacted within five (5) days after the date of the first attempt to contact him/her, the FoodCircles LLC may cancel payment or select an alternate winner at their sole discretion.
            %li
              %h3 Winner Notification
              %p
                The potential winners will be notified via electronic correspondence (email, Facebook, or Twitter in most cases). Each winner (parent/legal guardian if a minor in his/her state of residence) will be required to submit a legal US address within five (5) days of the date notice or attempted notice is sent, in order to claim his/her prize. If a potential winner cannot be contacted, or fails to submit the address within the required time period (if applicable), or check is returned as undeliverable, potential winner forfeits prize. If the potential winner is at least 18 but still considered a minor in his/her jurisdiction of residence, FoodCircles LLC reserves the right to award the prize in the name of his/her parent or legal guardian, who will be required to submit the address on the potential winners behalf and fulfill any other requirements imposed on winner set forth herein. Potential winners must continue to comply with all terms and conditions of these Official Rules, and winning is
                contingent upon fulfilling all requirements. Prizes will be fulfilled within 10 weeks after the conclusion of The Great Race.
            %li
              %h3 Prizes
              Reimbursement check of meal purchased (up to stated limit)
